  "prompt": "Can I directly get an admission in 12th (Arts) after 10th (Maharashtra)?",
  "response": "Yes, you can directly get admission to the 12th grade (Arts stream) after completing your 10th grade in Maharashtra, but typically you would need to first complete the 11th grade. The standard progression in most educational systems, including Maharashtra's, involves completing the 11th grade before moving on to the 12th grade. \n\nHere's the typical pathway:\n1. Complete 10th grade.\n2. Apply for admission to 11th grade (also known as First Year Junior College or FYJC) in the Arts stream.\n3. Complete 11th grade.\n4. Proceed to 12th grade (Second Year Junior College or SYJC) in the Arts stream.\n\nIf you have any specific circumstances or educational policies in mind, it might be best to check with the school or college you are interested in or refer to the official guidelines provided by the Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education (MSBSHSE).",
